<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <meta name="description" content="">
    <meta name="author" content="">

    <title>Aircloak â€“ Please upgrade your Aircloak</title>
    <link rel="shortcut icon" href="<%= static_path(@conn, "/images/favicon.ico") %>" type="image/x-icon">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="<%= static_path(@conn, "/css/vendor.css") %>">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="<%= static_path(@conn, "/css/app.css") %>">
  </head>

  <body class="outdated">
    <div class="body-wrapper">
      <div class="container">

        <p class="alert alert-info" role="alert"><%= get_flash(@conn, :info) %></p>
        <p class="alert alert-danger" role="alert"><%= get_flash(@conn, :error) %></p>

        <main role="main">
          <div class="col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-2">
            <h1>Please update your Aircloak</h1>

            <h2>What is the problem</h2>

            <p>
              Your Aircloak installation is running version <code><%= AirWeb.SharedView.version() %></code>
              which expired on <%= expiry_date() %>.
            </p>

            <p>
              This can happen for one of two reasons:
            </p>

            <ul>
              <li>You are significantly behind the official release schedule, and run a version that is no longer supported.</li>
              <li>Your license expired.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>How do I fix it</h2>

            <p>
              To resume operation, please update the version of your system that you are running.
              This can be done by pulling a more recent version of the <code>air</code> and <code>cloak</code>
              containers from the Aircloak registry and restarting your Aircloak instance.
            </p>

            <p>
              If you are using plain docker, the following set of commands should bring your system back up again:
            </p>

            <pre>
docker pull quay.io/aircloak/air:latest
docker pull quay.io/aircloak/cloak:latest

docker restart air
docker restart cloak</pre>

            <h2>Why is this happening</h2>

            <p>
              All Aircloak releases expire after a set amount of time.
              This ensures that you run a system with the strongest and most recent
              anonymization technology that we have to offer.
            </p>

            <p>
              Newer versions also contain important security fixes in the Linux subsystem used.
              It is recommended that you always run the latest version available,
              but ample time is provided so you can upgrade your installation on a schedule matching
              your internal requirements.
            </p>


            <h2>I need help</h2>

            <p>
              If you have questions or need help upgrading your system, please contact support on
              <a href="mailto:support@aircloak.com">support@aircloak.com</a>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </main>

      </div> <!-- /container -->
    </div>

    <script src="<%= static_path(@conn, "/js/app.js") %>"></script>
  </body>
</html>
